('St Mary the Virgin Handsworth','HMRC Registered',2956597,'cbfbac131d535393970492ae85e06e7f','Dear Friends, welcome to St Mary’s, described as “The Little Gem of South East Sheffield”, with its architectural features, quirks and connections to political power, civil and industrial progress. Visit our website’s homepage for more information. Although we are full of heritage we are a working church, offering worship and sharing in many people’s important life events such as baptism’s weddings and funerals. We play an active role in the community through a dedicated group of church members, from visiting the bereaved to running various children’s and youth groups, from supporting our lunch club, dementia café and social café to holding healing services, from having a community garden to supporting children abroad, from supporting a group for parents with children with high complex needs to flower arranging. In short, we are a group of Christians who keep sane in our topsy turvy world though our worship and fellowship. With this comes an established passion for helping to improve the lives of others in the community whether of faith or not.We don’t just maintain a 850yr church, full of heritage. We play our part in improving the lives of others through volunteers and our community centre. “Lunch Club has been a life saver”, Robert. “The Afternoon Tea helped me feel good again after my wife died”, Jack. “Understanding I’m the glue holding my family together I need to look after myself to be able to look after them”, Tracey. Your support can help us in this. Thank you','https://www.justgiving.com/stmarythevirginhandsworth','https://images.justgiving.com/image/','Sheffield','S13 9BZ',0,NULL,'GB'),
